abstract: Pressed about his decades-old opposition to same-sex marriage, Mr. Biden pushed back, saying he didn’t “have to evolve.”
snippet: Pressed about his decades-old opposition to same-sex marriage, Mr. Biden pushed back, saying he didn’t “have to evolve.”
lead_paragraph: CEDAR RAPIDS, Iowa — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. found himself fending off new questions about his decades-long record on lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender issues, in a testy exchange with a moderator who described his treatment of her as “condescending.”

abstract: Mayor Bill de Blasio of New York City, whose run for the Democratic nomination was often described as quixotic, never gained traction.
snippet: Mayor Bill de Blasio of New York City, whose run for the Democratic nomination was often described as quixotic, never gained traction.
lead_paragraph: Mayor Bill de Blasio, who entered the Democratic presidential race on the premise that his brand of liberal urban leadership in New York City could appeal on a national scale, said on Friday that he was ending his candidacy.

headline_main: Young Voters Still ‘Feel the Bern,’ but Not Just for Bernie Sanders Anymore
headline_print_headline: They Still Love Bernie, But This Time Around He’s Got Competition

abstract: A look back at American politics from the year 2050.
snippet: A look back at American politics from the year 2050.
lead_paragraph: A crisis of legitimacy swept across American politics in the second decade of the 21st century. Many people had the general conviction that the old order was corrupt and incompetent. There was an inchoate desire for some radical transformation. This mood swept the Republican Party in 2016 as Donald Trump eviscerated the G.O.P. establishment and it swept through the Democratic Party in 2020.

abstract: To understand the competing Democratic health care plans, consider an elaborate home construction metaphor.
snippet: To understand the competing Democratic health care plans, consider an elaborate home construction metaphor.
lead_paragraph: Imagine the United States health care system as a sort of weird old house. There are various wings, added at different points in history, featuring different architectural styles.

abstract: In the Democratic primary, there have been clashes over the Obama administration’s policies. But even liberal voters who admire the former president prefer to look to the future.
snippet: In the Democratic primary, there have been clashes over the Obama administration’s policies. But even liberal voters who admire the former president prefer to look to the future.
lead_paragraph: In some of the tensest moments of the 2020 debates, a viewer might have concluded that Democrats were poised for a large-scale clash over the legacy of President Barack Obama.

abstract: A melancholic Swedish sci-fi movie hits Hulu. And several Democratic presidential candidates gather for a climate forum.
snippet: A melancholic Swedish sci-fi movie hits Hulu. And several Democratic presidential candidates gather for a climate forum.
lead_paragraph: ANIARA (2019) Stream on Hulu; Rent on Amazon, Google Play, iTunes, Vudu and YouTube. This sci-fi drama from the directors Pella Kagerman and Hugo Lilja is based on a downbeat 1956 poem by the Swedish Nobel laureate Harry Martinson. Like its source material, the movie tells a story that is, despite being about humans traveling beyond the confines of earth’s atmosphere, supremely claustrophobic: It centers on a spaceship knocked off course, out of fuel and running out of hope. The crew of the ship, which had left an earth in environmental ruin and was bound for a human colony on Mars, includes MR (Emelie Jonsson), the story’s protagonist, whose situation becomes increasingly grim. “At times, the commitment to bleakness feels artistically admirable,” Teo Bugbee wrote in her review for The New York Times. “The film unblinkingly faces the void, and it refuses to console the audience, which has come along for the ride. But mostly, this is a movie that simulates the experience of losing the will to live, a daunting premise even for the bravest voyagers.”

abstract: “Sunnyside” is about trying to navigate the United States citizenship process, but its aims are more comic than didactic.

lead_paragraph: Kal Penn took a two-year sabbatical from acting to work in President Barack Obama’s White House, so you would be forgiven for assuming that he’s trying to make a political point with his new television series, “Sunnyside.”

abstract: How teachers, hotel workers and supermarket cashiers inspired 50,000 General Motors workers to go on strike.
snippet: How teachers, hotel workers and supermarket cashiers inspired 50,000 General Motors workers to go on strike.
lead_paragraph: Successful strikes beget more strikes. When nearly 50,000 General Motors workers walked out at 11:59 p.m. Sunday, it was just the latest in the largest burst of strikes in decades. Last year’s victorious teachers’ strike in West Virginia was the initial spark, helping inspire statewide walkouts in Oklahoma and Arizona as well as strikes in Kentucky, Colorado and Los Angeles.
